JavaScript
-developed by circa 1995 by Brendan Eich at Netscape Communications as the scripting language for the
Netscape Navigator Browser
-formerly called Mocha then LiveScript then JavaScript
-standardized by ECMA International as ECMAScript
-externally link to HTML(you can place it anywhere)
- Linked/Embedded in web pages using the &lt;script&gt; element
 Linked:

&lt;script type=”text/javascript” src=”scripts.js” /&gt; &lt;/script&gt;
 Embedded (either in the &lt;head&gt; or the &lt;body&gt; element)

&lt;script type=”text/javascript”&gt;
&lt;!—hidescript from non-JavaScript browsers…
/* script code goes here */
//end of scripting hiding … -- &gt;
&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;noscript&gt;
…content to show when scripting not available
&lt;/noscript&gt;

Defer- execute it at the end
Async-asynchronous
Window-global object
